I don't think my analysis was right. I found the following in the PDE ui plugin:

	class GroupByKeyComputer implements IGroupByKeyComputer {
		public Object computeGroupByKey(IMarker marker) {
			return marker;
		}

	}

However, in the PluginSearchLabelProvider, I found this:

		if (element instanceof ISearchResultViewEntry) {
			ISearchResultViewEntry entry = (ISearchResultViewEntry) element;

			IPluginObject object = (IPluginObject)entry.getGroupByKey();

This can only work because we acutally have the shortcut of
ISearchResultView.addMatch(String description, Object groupByKey, IResource
resource, IMarker marker).
I.E. what you return from getGroupByKey must always be the same as what is
passed into addMatch(...)

As far as I'm concerned, this is now again a PDE bug.
